      { q: 'A galaxy has a redshift z = 0.05. Given H₀ = 70 km s⁻¹ Mpc⁻¹, estimate the distance to this galaxy.', marks: 3, tier: 'amber', modelAnswer: '• Recessional velocity v = zc = 0.05 × 3.0 × 10⁵ = 15,000 km s⁻¹ (1)\\n• Hubble\'s law: d = v/H₀ = 15,000 / 70 (1)\\n• d = 214 Mpc (1)' },
      { q: 'State the Stefan-Boltzmann law and use it to explain why a red giant can be more luminous than a hotter main sequence star.', marks: 3, tier: 'amber', modelAnswer: '• L = σAT⁴ = 4πr²σT⁴ (Stefan-Boltzmann law relates luminosity to surface area and temperature) (1)\\n• Luminosity depends on both temperature and radius (surface area) (1)\\n• A red giant has a much larger radius than a main sequence star, so despite its lower temperature, its much greater surface area gives it a higher luminosity (1)' }
