      { q: 'A sample of iodine-131 (half-life 8.02 days) has an initial activity of 3.7 × 10⁸ Bq. It is used in medical treatment and the safe disposal level is 1.0 × 10⁴ Bq. Calculate how many days must pass before the sample can be safely disposed of. State any assumptions.', marks: 6, tier: 'red', modelAnswer: '• λ = ln2 / t½ = 0.693 / 8.02 = 0.0864 day⁻¹ (1)\\n• A = A₀e^(−λt), so t = −ln(A/A₀) / λ (1)\\n• t = −ln(1.0 × 10⁴ / 3.7 × 10⁸) / 0.0864 (1)\\n• t = −ln(2.70 × 10⁻⁵) / 0.0864 = −(−10.52) / 0.0864 (1)\\n• t = 121.8 days ≈ 122 days (1)\\n• Assumptions: the only radioactive isotope present is I-131; no other sources contribute to activity; the sample is not replenished (1)' }
