      { q: 'State what is meant by gravitational potential at a point in a gravitational field.', marks: 2, tier: 'green', modelAnswer: '• Gravitational potential at a point is the work done per unit mass (1)\\n• in bringing a small test mass from infinity to that point (it is always negative) (1)' }
